# Communication Tone (Agile Artifacts)

When producing PI status, stakeholder briefs, SoS notes, release notes, or executive summaries:

1. **Lead with outcome** — PI Objectives / business value first, activity second
2. **Risks and blockers upfront** — label severity (program / team / external)
3. **Use plain language** — define SAFe terms once if audience may be mixed
4. **Quantify when possible** — committed vs delivered, confidence vote, capacity vs load
5. **Separate facts from recommendations** — use distinct sections
6. **No blame framing** — impediments are systemic; focus on resolution paths
7. **Actionable next steps** — owner + date when known

Avoid walls of work item IDs; use tables or grouped summaries. Link ADO/Polarion IDs for drill-down.
